gurmukhi: kiRpwx pwx Dwir kY ]cly blI pukwir kY ]
transliteration: Kridaan Paan Ddaar(i) Kai|| Chale Balipudaar(i) Kai||
translation: Holding their swords in their hands, the mighty warriors marched forward with loud shouts;

gurmukhi: su mwir mwir BwKhI ]sroG sRox cwKhI ]12]
transliteration: Su Daar(i) Daar(i) Bhaakh-hee|| Darogh Sron Chaakh-hee||12||
translation: They uttered “kill, kill” and their arrows were drinking blood.12.

gurmukhi: sMjoie sYhQIn lY ]cVy su bIr ros kY ]
transliteration: Sanjoe Saihtheen Lai|| Chade Su Beer Ros Kai||
translation: Wearing their armour and holding their daggers, the warriors in great ire moved forward.

transliteration: Chataak Chaabkan Outhe|| Sahansra Saaekan Bouthe||13||
translation: The blows of whips horses produced knocking sounds and thousands of arrows flew out (from the bows).13.

transliteration: Bhae Ek Thaure|| Sabhai Soor Daure||
translation: All the warriors ran and gathered at one place.

transliteration: Layo Gher Raamannd|| Ghata Soor Syaamannd||14||
translation: And the besieged Parashurama, just as the clouds besiege the sun.14.
With the crackling of bows a queer sound was produced,

transliteration: Ghataa Jaan(i) Sayaahan|| Chadio Tio Sipaahan||15||
translation: And the army swarmed like the dark clouds.15.

transliteration: Bhae Naad Banke|| Su Selan Dhamannde||
translation: With the clattering of the daggers, a queer sound was produced,
